com.camerontec.catalys.server.collection

Class UnboundedPersistentBlockingQueue<E>

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.camerontec.catalys.server.collection.PersistentBlockingQueueBase<E>
      • com.camerontec.catalys.server.collection.UnboundedPersistentBlockingQueue<E>
  • Type Parameters:
    E - The element type.
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    IPeekableBlockingQueue<E>, Iterable<E>, Collection<E>, BlockingQueue<E>, Queue<E>

    public final class UnboundedPersistentBlockingQueue<E>
extends PersistentBlockingQueueBase<E>
    An unbounded blocking queue implementation which stores its elements persistently.

    This implementation uses two underlying collections:

    • A high capacity list for storing elements persistently
    • A map containing only a single key/value pair, representing the current head index into the elements list. Caching is enabled since the head index is read (and updated) frequently.

    This implementation has the following characteristics:

    • No elements added to this queue are ever removed from the underlying persistent list.
    • The head index is maintained persistently and incremented to simulate element removal
    • The capacity of the queue is limited only by the underlying persistence mechanism.

    This implementation supports iteration in the presence of concurrent modification.

    See Also:
    ICollectionRegistry, CollectionProperties, IBytesSegmentExternalizer, BoundedPersistentBlockingQueue
